#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:1
msgid "E0017"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:3
msgid "Warning name: `ambiguous_loop_argument`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:5
msgid ""
"The usage of identifier is ambiguous. If it refers to the loop variable, "
"please use `as <id>` to bind it in the pattern. If it refers to the "
"original value of the variable before entering the loop, please bind it "
"to a new binder outside the loop."
msgstr ""
"标识符的使用存在歧义。如果它指的是循环变量，请使用 `as <id>` "
"在模式中绑定它。如果它指的是变量在进入循环前的原始值，请在循环外部将其绑定到一个新的绑定器。"

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:11
msgid ""
"This warning is tied to the deprecated `loop` syntax. Current MoonBit "
"also reports `deprecated_syntax` for that construct, so this "
"compatibility page has no checked source example."
msgstr ""
"这个警告与已弃用的 `loop` 语法相关。当前 MoonBit 也会对该构造报告 "
"`deprecated_syntax`，因此这个兼容性页面没有经过检查的源代码示例。"

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:16
msgid "Suggestion"
msgstr "建议"

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:18
msgid "Rewrite old `loop` code with a `for` loop when possible. For example:"
msgstr "尽可能将旧的 `loop` 代码改写为 `for` 循环。例如："

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:20
msgid ""
"let text : StringView = \"asdf\"\n"
"for i = 0; i < text.length(); i = i + 1 {\n"
"  println(text[i:])\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:27
msgid ""
"If you are maintaining existing `loop` code, make the intended binding "
"explicit: use `as <id>` when you mean the loop variable, or bind the "
"original value to a different name before entering the loop."
msgstr ""
"如果你在维护现有的 `loop` 代码，请明确预期的绑定：当你指的是循环变量时使用 "
"`as <id>`；当你指的是原始值时，在进入循环前将其绑定到另一个名称。"

#~ msgid "Erroneous example"
#~ msgstr "错误示例"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "///|\n"
#~ "fn main {\n"
#~ "  let a : StringView = \"asdf\"\n"
#~ "  loop a {\n"
#~ "    [_, .. d] => {\n"
#~ "      println(a)\n"
#~ "      //      ^\n"
#~ "      // Warning: The usage of 'a'"
#~ " is ambiguous. If it refers to "
#~ "the loop\n"
#~ "      // variable, please use `as "
#~ "a` to bind it in the pattern. "
#~ "If it refers to\n"
#~ "      // the original value of 'a'"
#~ " before entering the loop, please "
#~ "bind it to a\n"
#~ "      // new binder outside the loop.\n"
#~ "      continue d\n"
#~ "    }\n"
#~ "    [] => ()\n"
#~ "  }\n"
#~ "}\n"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid "Output:"
#~ msgstr "输出："

#~ msgid ""
#~ "asdf\n"
#~ "asdf\n"
#~ "asdf\n"
#~ "asdf\n"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Because `a` refers to the value of"
#~ " `a` before entering the loop, "
#~ "therefore the value is always the "
#~ "same."
#~ msgstr "因为 `a` 指的是进入循环前的 `a` 的值，因此该值始终相同。"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Since `loop` syntax will be removed "
#~ "soon, prefer rewriting new code with "
#~ "a `for` loop when possible. For "
#~ "example, this code can be written "
#~ "as:"
#~ msgstr "由于 `loop` 语法很快会被移除，若条件允许，建议优先将新代码改写为 `for` 循环。例如，这段代码可以写成："

#~ msgid ""
#~ "If you are maintaining existing `loop`"
#~ " code, and you want to refer to"
#~ " the loop variable that changes with"
#~ " loop iterations, use `as <id>` to"
#~ " bind it in the pattern."
#~ msgstr "如果你是在维护现有的 `loop` 代码，并且想引用随循环迭代而变化的循环变量，请使用 `as <id>` 在模式中绑定它。"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "///|\n"
#~ "fn main {\n"
#~ "  let a : StringView = \"asdf\"\n"
#~ "  loop a {\n"
#~ "    [_, .. d] as a => {\n"
#~ "      println(a)\n"
#~ "      continue d\n"
#~ "    }\n"
#~ "    [] => ()\n"
#~ "  }\n"
#~ "}\n"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "asdf\n"
#~ "sdf\n"
#~ "df\n"
#~ "f\n"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Or, if you want to refer to "
#~ "the original value of the variable "
#~ "before entering the loop, explicitly "
#~ "bind it to another name outside "
#~ "the loop."
#~ msgstr "或者，如果你想在进入循环之前引用变量的原始值，可以显式地将其绑定到循环外的另一个名称。"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "///|\n"
#~ "fn main {\n"
#~ "  let a : StringView = \"asdf\"\n"
#~ "  let b = a\n"
#~ "  loop a {\n"
#~ "    [_, .. d] => {\n"
#~ "      println(b)\n"
#~ "      continue d\n"
#~ "    }\n"
#~ "    [] => ()\n"
#~ "  }\n"
